<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 3:38PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Davidson and
northwestern Randolph Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 338 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Bermuda Run, or 8 miles east of Mocksville, moving
southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
High Point, Lexington, Thomasville, Linwood, Arcadia, Gordontown,
High Rock Boat Dock Marina, Welcome, Nc Wildlife Access Boat Launch
and High Rock Lake Marina &amp; Campground.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
